text: what brings you in today
I'm just feeling worn out all the time. It's hard to keep up with things.
when did this start
It started getting worse after I stopped working.
why and when did you stop working
I stopped working because I was too weak and tired to keep up. It's been a while now.
do you have any other conditions
I've had high blood pressure since my thirties.
has anything made the tiredness better
Not really. I just feel worn out no matter what.
has anything made it worse
The swelling in my legs seems to make it worse, and I get dizzy if I move too fast.
have you noticed any shortness of breath
Yeah, I get short of breath when I walk too far or climb stairs.
have you noticed any chest pain
No, I haven't had any chest pain.
have you noticed anything getting worse at night
I'm sorry, I had trouble understanding you. Could you please rephrase that?
do you have any issues sleeping at all
Yeah, I can't sleep much anymore. My legs won't stop moving, and I wake up covered in this white, powdery stuff on my skin.
can you lay flat at night with no issues
I can lay flat, but my legs twitch a lot, which makes it hard to get comfortable and stay asleep.
have you noticed any cough
No, I haven't noticed any cough.
house swollen all your ankles
My legs swell up bad, sometimes past my knees, and it can be hard to bend them.
do you feel the dizziness constantly or only when you exert yourself
I mostly feel dizzy if I stand up too fast or move around too quickly.
have you noticed any changes with urinary habits
I don't pee as much as I used to, and sometimes it's darker than normal.
does it hurt when you when you urinate
No, it doesn't hurt when I urinate.
you get up a lot of night do you use the bathroom
No, I don't get up a lot at night to use the bathroom.
have you noticed any blood in your urine
No, I haven't noticed any blood in my urine.
what color is your urine
Sometimes it's darker than normal.
do you eat beets
No, I don't eat beets.
what medications are you taking right now
I have a whole bunch of medicines I'm on that I can't pronounce. My girlfriend makes me keep a list in my wallet.
do you know what medications are on for your blood pressure
Yeah, I'm on a few for my blood pressure, like furosemide, nifedipine, clonidine patch, and atenolol.
does anything run in the family
Yeah, my dad had high blood pressure and diabetes, and my mom had breast cancer.
you take any over the counter medications
I take aspirin and iron, but that's about it.
do you smoke at all or drink any alcohol
I don't smoke, and I only drink a few beers on Fridays, but not often.
have you ever had surgery for anything or ever been in the hospital
I haven't had surgery, but I was in the hospital for lung congestion before. I also had a mild stroke a while back.
when did the lung congestion happen if you had to give me a date
I don't remember the exact date, but it was a while back before the stroke.
when was the stroke
The stroke happened a while back, but I can't recall the exact date. It caused temporary weakness on my left side, but it got better.
have you noticed any nausea or vomiting at all
Yeah, I feel nauseated most days and have vomited a few times lately.
have you noticed a metallic taste at all
Yeah, everything I eat tastes like metal.
have you noticed any bruising
Yeah, bruises just show up on their own lately.
